    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-11-24T19:55:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-11-24T19:55:00-05:00" n="163"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d163">
                <head>163. Notes of Telephone Conversation Between the President’s Assistant for
                    National Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_KHA1" type="from"
                        >Kissinger</persName>) and the British Ambassador (<persName
                        corresp="#p_TSE1" type="to">Tomkins</persName>)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d163fn1">Source: Library of Congress, Manuscript Division, <persName
                            corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName> Papers, Box 361, Telephone
                        Conversations, Chronological File, 18–28 November 1969. No classification
                        marking.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d163fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName> informed <persName
                            corresp="#p_TSE1">Tomkins</persName> about the decision to be announced
                        the next day concerning chemical and biological weapons.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1969-11-24T19:55:00-05:00">November 24, 1969, 7:55 p.m.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> wanted to tell T now, on a personal basis that
                    we are going to make an announcement tomorrow about our policy with regard to
                    biological and chemical warfare. <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said we are
                    going to endorse the principles of the United Kingdom draft convention. And we
                    will offer to work out specific provisions with you. T asked if we would
                    announce the last part. <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said yes. <gloss
                        target="#t_K1">K</gloss> asked that T make sure the Prime Minister knows;
                        <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> asked that he handle it on a personal basis
                    between the President and the Prime Minister. T said he would and that he was
                    most grateful to <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss>.</p>
            </div>
